profile_short_name:Catimor NAT Yunnan v4
profile_designer:Claude
profile_description:Yunnan Pu'er Catimor Natural 1650m\vMoisture: 11.5% | Density: 759g/L\vLoad: 120g\v\vVersion 4 - Sweetness optimization based on V3 (log0080)\v\vV3 results (log0080 - best roast so far):\v- FC clearly detected at ~190C/310s (ROR crash 21->1.3, 93% drop)\v- Dev ratio 20.3%, weight loss 9.2%, total time 6:24\v- Profile tracking excellent: mean +0.3C, max cold -5.3C\v- Flavor: rich floral/fruit, full body, clean, fruit acid\v- Issue: sweetness decreased vs V2 -> end temp 203.3C\v  is ~2C past sweetness peak (~200-201C)\v- Issue: end-of-roast ROR sprint 10->14->3 in last 15s\v  (surface over-roasting risk)\v\vV4 changes:\v1. expect_fc: 195 -> 192 (actual FC ~190C, 2C margin)\v2. roast_levels: all -1C (197-209C) -> back to sweetness window\v3. Endpoint: 390s/206C -> 395s/204C (lower temp preserves\v   sweetness, +5s maintains development)\v4. FC-to-endpoint slope gentler (10C/95s vs 12C/90s)\v   to suppress end-of-roast ROR sprint\v5. FC area point: 194 -> 193C (align with lower expect_fc)\v\vRecommended Levels:\v  Nordic Light: Level 1.0 (~197C)\v  Light Filter: Level 1.5 (~199C)\v  Sweet Balanced: Level 2.0 (~201C) <- Target\v  Full Body: Level 2.5 (~203C)\v\vTarget: Level 2.0 (201C)\vExpected total time: 6:30-6:50\vExpected weight loss: 10-12%\vExpected dev ratio: 17-20%\v\vCatimor varietal note: tail bitterness is inherent\v(Robusta heritage, high chlorogenic acid). Not a\vroast defect - do not chase it.\v
